1
00:00:01,481 --> 00:00:05,110
<i>Ed, it was three on his right
and two on his left.</i>

2
00:00:05,185 --> 00:00:09,815
No, Chris, it was definitely
one on his left.

3
00:00:09,890 --> 00:00:14,259
Holling, how many toes did Marty
Sorenson lose that time he got frostbite?

4
00:00:14,328 --> 00:00:17,957
Well, let's see. It was one on his
left and two on his right, wasn't it?

5
00:00:18,031 --> 00:00:20,829
Well, I don't believe it.

6
00:00:20,901 --> 00:00:22,835
- Hello, Edna.
- Holling.

7
00:00:22,903 --> 00:00:24,871
<i>Been a while.
Yes, it has.</i>

8
00:00:24,938 --> 00:00:27,702
Fellas, you know Edna Hancock.

9
00:00:27,774 --> 00:00:30,299
<i>Lives over next to Maurice.</i>

10
00:00:30,377 --> 00:00:32,311
Hi.
Well, almost next to him.

11
00:00:32,379 --> 00:00:35,542
What is it, four miles
from door to door?

12
00:00:35,615 --> 00:00:38,641
<i>Five.
Maurice has his 15,000 acres,</i>

13
00:00:38,719 --> 00:00:41,415
- and you have what, Edna, 10?
- Twelve.

14
00:00:41,488 --> 00:00:43,649
<i>12,000 acres. My gosh.</i>

15
00:00:43,724 --> 00:00:45,749
It's good to see ya.

16
00:00:45,826 --> 00:00:50,126
I think I still have
some of that single malt you like.

17
00:00:50,197 --> 00:00:52,358
Nobody calls for this very often.

18
00:00:52,432 --> 00:00:54,923
Make it a double?
Too late for that.

19
00:00:55,001 --> 00:00:58,562
I beg your pardon?
Too late for single malt, Holling.

20
00:00:58,638 --> 00:01:00,572
Too late for a lot of things.

21
00:01:00,640 --> 00:01:05,009
l-I don't follow you. I'm running
for mayor, Holling, against you.

22
00:01:05,078 --> 00:01:06,909
Why?
Why?

23
00:01:06,980 --> 00:01:10,416
Five years ago, you could
have given me a stop sign.

24
00:01:10,484 --> 00:01:12,418
Now it's too late
for that too.

25
00:01:12,486 --> 00:01:16,445
Five years ago? I was sitting right
here. You said you'd look into it.

26
00:01:16,523 --> 00:01:18,787
But you didn't now,
did you?

27
00:01:18,859 --> 00:01:21,589
Well, l-I must have
forgotten is all, Edna.

28
00:01:21,661 --> 00:01:24,129
Well, it won't happen again.

29
00:01:24,197 --> 00:01:26,131
See you on election day.

30
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:34,074
